		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				Lets say two players are after the same mob. A Wizard and a druid. <br>  <br> Wizards stops when in range, starts casting his first spell. The druid seeing this, presses forward, runs up and aggros the mob before the Wizard's spell goes off. <br>  <br> Who's mob is it? The one who actually made contact first, or the one who started casting on it first? <br>  <br> My personal feeling is that it's a tie. They should both go for it. <br>  <br> Levels being equal, the Wizard is probably going to do 51% of the damage thus taking the xp. The druid is going to probably yell that he was KS'd. <br>  <br> So the basic question is, should a caster intentionally interupt their spell on a mob if someone actaully makes physical contact before their spell goes off? <br>  <br> Curious what other players think.
						<p><span class="SignatureTitle">-----signature-----</span>
