				The general rule is the mobs belongs to whoever engages it first. If someone agros a mob while I'm casting I will just duck. My spell hadn't landed yet therefore I have not engaged the mob yet. <br>  <br> Its first agro not first damage. You can be pulling a mob without damageing it. I try my best not to get in melee range when I pull with my Monk. If my shurken doesn't hit I didn't do any damage, but the mob is surely my groups. No one has the right to just take your pulls. <br>  <br> If the Druid was doing it intentionally thats another story. I would let him snare it and chain nuke then.		

